 On 1 January 2019, various amendments came into play in relation to both the Basic Conditions of Employment Act and the Unemployment Insurance Act pertaining to the leave which an employee may take when his or her child is born or adopted. Three additional categories of leave is applicable: Parental Leave: Adoption Leave Commissioning Parent Parental Leave Given the changes in categories of leave relating to the birth of a child, it is important that employment contracts and policies are properly updated. For assistance in this regard, please do not hesitate to contact Goldberg & De Villiers, Tracey Mouton, telephone number (041) 501 9818, e-mail address traceym@goldlaw.co.za. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. 